article.headline: Savannah St. 67, Allen 52
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- Joshua Obiajunwa scored 12 of his 22 points in the first seven minutes to lead Savannah State to a 67-52 victory over Allen on Saturday. Obiajunwa also had 12 rebounds, two blocked shots and three steals as the Tigers (11-17) led all the way, building a 38-16 halftime advantage. Joshua Williams led Allen (6-15) with 15 points and eight rebounds. Joseph Flegler added 16 points for the Tigers, who four times in the second half built a 26-point lead, the last on a pair of free throws by Flegler that made it 52-26 with 14:42 left in the game.
